I started doing evp&#39;s about a year ago. I use an Olympus digital 
recorder. I have had some luck. I was given a copy of Gold Wave recently 
and don&#39;t know the program yet. I saw that someone offered up a link to 
a free tool but I could only find copies that cost.

About three weeks ago I had a friend over. He has a pretty successful 
investigative team in my area. One of his members brought the &#39;Franks 
box&#39; to show me since he knows of my interest in ITC. We didn&#39;t use it 
however. They had among other instruments, a K-II emf meter. Actually 
they had about 3 meters of different types. I asked if he could use the 
box but he said he didn&#39;t know it well enough yet to label anything 
paranormal. He did turn it on and there was a lot of noise and chatter.  
They did quit a few videos as well. The results were not that favorable 
with the video but the emf showed allot of activity. We were able to 
&#39;communicate&#39; using the K-II and asking yes - no questions. I don&#39;t have 
the evp&#39;s yet. I do have my own evp&#39;s from my apartment but not from 
that night. I also have some from a couple cemeteries that I did. I like 
going out by myself which I guess is a big no no in the field of 
paranormal investigation but it hasn&#39;t bothered me much at all.

I am trying to get his friend to bring the box back over. I became 
interested in ITC about 11 years ago but never really involved myself 
into it. Someone took a picture of me in my kitchen. When the film was 
developed, a face appeared in the window behind me. There was no way a 
person could have been outside my apartment window. I started doing some 
research on line and that was how I found out about ITC and evp. A few 
years later I saw White Noise and my interest was sparked all over 
again. I have read about the &#39;Brown box&#39; and was really excited when my 
buddies friend brought over &#39;Franks box&#39;. With the popularity of all the 
paranormal shows and groups I have decided to concentrate on evp. I am 
now considered an &#39;investigator in training&#39; but my interest are purely 
personal.

I am assuming that you are the &#39;Frank&#39; of my friends &#39;Frank&#39;s box&#39;. I 
was really surprised at the coincident when I joined this evp group to 
find out that it is your group.

I hope to learn allot from this group and thanks for having me as a member.

Mick

PS - I was considering moving to Florida but after reading all these 
&#39;bog&#39; post, I may move west.

